  "text": "# Envoy HTTP Filter Factory Registration and Instantiation Tracing\n\n## Overview\n\nHTTP filter factory registration and instantiation in Envoy follows a well-defined architecture:\n\n1. **Factory Definition and Registration**: Filter factories are defined as classes inheriting from `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` (envoy/server/filter_config.h) and registered globally via the `REGISTER_FACTORY` macro (envoy/registry/registry.h).\n\n2. **Configuration-Time Factory Creation**: When Envoy loads configuration, `FilterChainHelper` (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h) processes HTTP filter configurations. The `processFilter` method retrieves the registered factory from `FactoryRegistry` and calls `createFilterFactoryFromProto` to create a `FilterFactoryCb` callback.\n\n3. **Per-Connection Filter Chain Creation**: When a new HTTP stream arrives, `FilterManager::createFilterChain` (source/common/http/filter_manager.cc) is called. This invokes the `FilterChainFactory::createFilterChain` method, which passes control to `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories` (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc).\n\n4. **Per-Request Filter Instantiation**: `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories` iterates through the list of filter factories and calls `FilterChainManager::applyFilterFactoryCb` for each one. The `FilterChainManager` implementation in `FilterManager` delegates to `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl::addStreamDecoderFilter` (source/common/http/filter_manager.h), which creates actual filter instances (e.g., `StreamDecoderFilterSharedPtr`) and wraps them in `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter` structures.\n\n## Key Components\n\n### Filter Factory Registry\n- **`FactoryRegistry<Base>`** (envoy/registry/registry.h): Template-based global registry storing factory instances indexed by name\n- **`RegisterFactory<T, Base>`** (envoy/registry/registry.h): Template class used via `REGISTER_FACTORY` macro to register factory instances at static initialization time\n- **`REGISTER_FACTORY` macro** (envoy/registry/registry.h): Creates a static `RegisterFactory` instance that registers the factory in `FactoryRegistry`\n\n### Filter Factory Base Classes\n- **`NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory`** (envoy/server/filter_config.h): Pure virtual interface defining `createFilterFactoryFromProto` method that factories must implement\n- **`HttpFilterConfigFactoryBase`** (envoy/server/filter_config.h): Base class extending `ProtocolOptionsFactory` providing common functionality\n- **`FactoryBase<ConfigProto, RouteConfigProto>`** (source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h): Template class extending both `CommonFactoryBase` and `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory`, providing type-safe wrapper methods\n- **`CommonFactoryBase<ConfigProto, RouteConfigProto>`** (source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h): Implements common factory functionality like protobuf message creation and validation\n\n### Filter Factory Callbacks\n- **`FilterFactoryCb`** (envoy/http/filter_factory.h): Type alias for `std::function<void(FilterChainFactoryCallbacks& callbacks)>` - the actual callback invoked per-stream to instantiate filters\n- **`FilterContext`** (envoy/http/filter_factory.h): Carries contextual information (config name, filter name) to the filter instantiation callback\n\n### Filter Chain Creation and Instantiation\n- **`FilterChainFactory`** (envoy/http/filter_factory.h): Pure virtual interface with `createFilterChain` method\n- **`FilterChainManager`** (envoy/http/filter_factory.h): Pure virtual interface with `applyFilterFactoryCb` method that the factory calls to instantiate filters\n- **`FilterManager`** (source/common/http/filter_manager.h): Implements both `FilterChainFactory` and `FilterChainManager`, managing filter chains for a stream\n- **`FilterChainHelper<FilterCtx, NeutralNamedHttpFilterFactory>`** (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h): Template processing HTTP filter configurations and creating `FilterFactoryCb` callbacks\n- **`FilterChainUtility`** (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h/cc): Utility with `createFilterChainForFactories` static method that iterates filter factories and calls their callbacks\n- **`FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl`** (source/common/http/filter_manager.h): Implements `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks`, providing methods (`addStreamDecoderFilter`, `addStreamEncoderFilter`, `addStreamFilter`) to instantiate actual filter objects and wrap them in `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter`/`ActiveStreamEncoderFilter`\n\n### Per-Request Filter Wrappers\n- **`ActiveStreamDecoderFilter`** (source/common/http/filter_manager.h): Wraps `StreamDecoderFilterSharedPtr` instances with callbacks and state management\n- **`ActiveStreamEncoderFilter`** (source/common/http/filter_manager.h): Wraps `StreamEncoderFilterSharedPtr` instances with callbacks and state management\n\n### Upstream HTTP Filter Support\n- **`FilterConfig`** (source/common/router/router.h): Router filter that implements `FilterChainFactory` for upstream HTTP filters, storing a `FilterFactoriesList` and delegating to `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories`\n\n## Example: Basic Auth Filter\n\n**BasicAuthFilterFactory** (source/extensions/filters/http/basic_auth/config.h/cc):\n1. Extends `FactoryBase` with protobuf config type\n2. Implements `createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped` returning a `FilterFactoryCb` lambda\n3. Lambda closure captures filter configuration and when invoked, calls `callbacks.addStreamDecoderFilter` with a new `BasicAuthFilter` instance\n4. Registered via `REGISTER_FACTORY(BasicAuthFilterFactory, Server::Configuration::NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory)` (source/extensions/filters/http/basic_auth/config.cc:86)\n\n## Execution Flow\n\n1. **Static Initialization**: `REGISTER_FACTORY` macro creates static `RegisterFactory` instance that calls `FactoryRegistry<NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory>::registerFactory` to store factory in global registry\n2. **Configuration Load**: `FilterChainHelper::p